verses.roman:
pūrve yabe subuddhi-rāya chilā gauḍe 'adhikāri'
husena-khāṅ 'saiyada' kare tāhāra cākarī

synonyms: pūrve—formerly; yabe—when; subuddhi-rāya—Subuddhi Rāya; chilā—resided; gauḍe—in Bengal; adhikārī—a very respectable man; husena-khāṅ—Nawab Hussain Khān; saiyada—named Saiyada; kare—performed; tāhāra cākarī—service of Subuddhi Rāya.
translation: Formerly Subuddhi Rāya had been a big landholder in Gauḍa-deśa [Bengal]. Saiyada Hussain Khān was then a servant of Subuddhi Rāya.
